    Association of cow's milk intake in early childhood with adiposity and cardiometabolic risk in early adolescence.
 Consumption of higher-fat cow's milk in early childhood was not associated with increased adiposity or adverse cardiometabolic health over a decade later. Our findings do not support current recommendations to consume lower-fat milk to reduce the risk of later obesity and adverse cardiometabolic outcomes. Clinical Trial Registry Number  NCT02820402 (
